              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " One fragment was detected in a",
                "delta-E-E telescope. The delta-E detector was an",
                "ionization chamber with a window of 300 mug/cm**2",
                "thickness of Hostaphan.",
                "The residual energy was measured with a solid state",
                "surface barrier detector of 450-mm**2.",
                "The second fragment was detected by a fast, position",
                "sensitive detector system, composed of a bi-dimensional",
                "drift chamber and a parallel plate avalanche counter,",
                "providing the time signal.The detector had a window of",
                " 300 mug/cm**2 thickness.The active area of the",
                "detector was 30*4 cm**2. The average angle between the",
                "small and large detector was 78-degree and it was kept",
                "constant in all measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " coincidence measurement of both O-16 fragments"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.The data were normalized relative to the",
                "Faraday cup reading. The absolute normalisation was",
                "obtained using the elastic scattering of O-16 on the",
                "Al-27 at 29, 45 and 65 MeV. After correcting for the",
                "average charge state in the Faraday cup, the",
                "normalization constants were consistent within 20%",
                "between the three energies.",
                "*By authors*.The double differential cross section",
                "vs Q is shown in fig.1 for different angles measured.",
                "The spectra are similar and show the following features",
                " -a peak at Q=0 MeV corresponding to the g.s-g.s",
                "transition,",
                " -a peak at Q approx.-(6-8)MeV corresponding to the",
                "excitation of one O-16 fragment into one of the levels",
                "of O-16 between 6 and 8 MeV",
                " - a peak around Q=-13 MeV corresponding to excitation",
                "of both O-fragments to one of the states around",
                "E-EXC=6-8 MeV,",
                " - a broad tail extending from Q=-16 to -20 MeV  is",
                "approximately the maximum Q value possible for this",
                "reaction and corresponds to a total kinetic energy in",
                "the final state close to the Coulomb barrier for two",
                "O-16 nuclei."
              ]
            }
          ],
